Reasoning: The paper deals with clustering algorithms and their performance under a specific querying model. This falls under the scope of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of an oracle and optimization of the clustering objective also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its methods against known correlation clustering algorithms, indicating a potential fit for computational complexity (cs.CC).
